`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- Perlin noise uses a seeded permutation table (Fisher-Yates shuffle with a PRNG) so the same worldSeed always produces the same gradient lattice, making all derived noise functions (fBm, ridged, domain warp) deterministic by construction.
- fBm sums octaves with halving amplitude and doubling frequency — normalizing by `maxValue` keeps output in [-1,1] regardless of octave count.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
