`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The offset `(x + 5.2, y + 1.3)` in domain warping is an Inigo Quilez technique — it breaks the symmetry between the X and Y warp vectors, preventing them from sampling the same noise value and creating a visually boring diagonal pattern.
- Ridged multifractal uses a `weight` that suppresses subsequent octaves in flat areas and amplifies them near ridges — this self-similarity feedback creates the characteristic sharp mountain spine appearance.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
